---
title: "Login — OAuth Authorization Code Flow"
---
%% TEMPLATE: sequence diagram — mermaid (frontmatter title must be line 1). For flows over
%% time between parties: auth/login, OAuth handshake, API request lifecycle. Solid (->>) =
%% call/request, dashed (-->>) = return/response (sequence arrows can't be colored). Label
%% every message. Use alt for conditions, loop for retries — nest at most one level deep.
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User
    participant Web as Web App
    participant Auth as OAuth Provider
    participant API as API

    User->>Web: Click "Log in"
    Web->>Auth: Redirect to /authorize
    Auth->>User: Show login + consent
    User->>Auth: Submit credentials
    Auth-->>Web: Redirect back with code

    Web->>Auth: Exchange code for token
    Auth-->>Web: Access token

    alt token valid
        Web->>API: GET /me (Bearer token)
        API-->>Web: 200 profile
    else token rejected
        API-->>Web: 401 Unauthorized
    end
